          <msContents>
            <summary>Two trimmed and mounted Qurʼān leaves written in gold. One leaf contains verses from al-Taghābun (second half of 4-first half of 9), the other leaf contains verses from al-Mulk (67), though they are out of order (the second half of verse 19-the first few words of 21, then, on the word 'rizqahu', changing it to 'rizqihi' and continuing with the end of verse 15 through to the first half of verse 18).</summary>
            <textLang mainLang="ara">Arabic</textLang>
